The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 50 killed in Pak violence 

 Dera Ismail Khan (Pakistan), April 4 (Reuters): Pakistani tribesmen battled foreign al Qaida-linked militants near the Afghan border today in heavy clashes that killed around 50 people, officials said. 

 The fighting began today when tribesmen attacked and captured a militant stronghold in a village near Wana. 

 Pacific quake 

 Washington (Reuters): An earthquake of 6.3 magnitude struck the Loyalty Islands of New Caledonia in the south Pacific on Wednesday, the US Geological Survey said. There were no reports of damage or injuries. 

 Phone flights 

 Washington (AP): The US Federal Communications Commission has officially rejected the idea of allowing airline passengers to use cellphones while in flight. 

 HK richest 

 Hong Kong (Reuters): Asias richest woman, Nina Wang, has died of an unspecified illness after reports she had been battling cancer. 




